20/03/2007
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Police in Kragujevac prevented an attempt to traffic several Albanian teenagers to Western Europe via Serbia on Monday (March 19th). 
Officials say four Albanians, between 14 and 16 years old, were found hidden in a vehicle driven by a Montenegrin citizen. 
The driver was arrested and faces charges of human trafficking.
Separately Monday, Croatian police announced that they smashed a human trafficking ring. 
On Sunday, police arrested two Croatian citizens who allegedly intended to smuggle nine Albanians and six Turkish nationals into the EU by truck. 
The arrests occurred near the eastern border with Serbia. 
(RTS, AFP - 19/03/07)
